The paper discusses the use of Sum-Product networks (SPNs) in probabilistic modeling and inference, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of EM algorithm and MPE inference, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with conditional independencies, which is a topic in probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the interpretation of SPNs as Bayesian networks, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CL, and cs.CV.
